sec.p:
Haigh (2010) has noted that the information gathering and sharing opportunities, referred to as participatory media, offered by the second generation of web design that allow for information sharing – known as web 2.0 – have expanded our horizons beyond academia to the whole of the global research and education community. Participatory media include (but are not limited to):


blogs;

wikis;

video blogs;

social networking sites (SNSs);

micro-blogging sites;

podcasts;

mashups.
